name: The desire became domesticated in all this brutality
description:
Sometimes in this brutality, my whole desire to live turns into an ivy growing inside me. It binds me, my youngity and my unborn childrens to my veins and squeezes all my womanhood. My veins can't pump anything but femininity into my heart. One by one, I give birth to all the atrocities that are not yet born within me.
Suddenly I'm growing enough to bring tears to your eyes, and I'm also getting small enough too to be the house of all this brutality.
